        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
        <h4 class="modal-title">The introduce about how to use this web app</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>There are three typing box in the middle of whole page.</p>
        <p> The Red box 'Players' is the place you can type the information of players you want to search. In addition, there are three small drop-down list that you can choose the searching type. 'Name' means the player's name, '#' means the hashtag and '@' means twitter screen names.
        </p>
        <p> The functions of the blue box and green box are the same of that of red box.
          The screen name typed in green box 'Authors of tweets' can be used to display that player's current club, position and birthday.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
